Method behavioural requirements:
- The string parameter `word` must not be null.
- The long result is the number of wonderful non-empty substrings in the string parameter `word`.
- Each occurrence of the same substring in the string parameter `word` must be counted separately.
- A substring is a contiguous sequence of characters in a string.
- A wonderful string is a string where at most one letter appears an odd number of times.
- The wonderful substrings must be counted based on the constraints specified in the business requirement.